{
  "texts": [
    "TN stands for true negatives, signifying the number of pixels correctly recognized as background in the segmentation result, consistent with background pixels in the true annotation.PR.",
    "Precision represents the proportion of correctly predicted positive samples by the model.",
    "Recall (also known as sensitivity) represents the proportion of true positive samples successfully detected by the model out of all actual positive samples.",
    "PR curve can be plotted by taking recall as the x-axis and precision as the y-axis.Precision = TP TP + FP, Recall = TP TP + FN.",
    "Intersection over union, also known as the Jaccard coefficient, is used to measure the overlap between the predicted result and the ground truth target."
  ]
}